0Saudi%20Arabian%20national%20on%20Saturday%20flew%20to%20India%2C%20entered%20the%20five-star%20hotel%20where%20UAE%20President%20Mohamed%20bin%20Zayed%20Al%20Nahyan%20was%20staying%2C%20and%20was%20stopped%20by%20security%20personnel%20while%20trying%20to%20approach%20him%20in%20the%20hotel%20lobby%20to%20seek%20help%20for%20his%20ailing%20brother%2C%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20man%2C%20reportedly%20a%20police%20officer%20from%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20reached%20the%20Taj%20Mansingh%20Hotel%20in%20central%20Delhi%20in%20a%20hotel%20car%20that%20had%20a%20G20%20security%20clearance%20sticker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20flown%20to%20Delhi%20recently%20and%20was%20staying%20at%20a%20hotel%20in%20Aerocity%2C%20which%20is%20near%20the%20Delhi%20airport%2C%20and%20wanted%20to%20meet%20the%20UAE%20crown%20prince%20to%20seek%20help%20for%20his%20brother%2C%20who%20is%20undergoing%20treatment%20for%20a%20terminal%20illness%20in%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20souces%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20spotted%20and%20approached%20the%20UAE%20President%20after%20waiting%20in%20the%20lobby%20of%20the%20hotel%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20but%20was%20stopped%20by%20the%20President's%20security%20detail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20an%20interaction%20with%20the%20UAE%20President's%20security%20in-charge%2C%20he%20was%20allowed%20to%20meet%20the%20UAE%20President.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20man%20was%20taken%20into%20custody%20by%20the%20Delhi%20police%2C%20and%20was%20let%20go%20after%20hours%20of%20interrogation%20by%20various%20investigative%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Delhi%20police%20had%20issued%20G20%20security%20clearance%20stickers%20for%20hotel%20taxis%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694418060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Fjlei7i1o_g20-security_625x300_07_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsaudi-cop-reaches-uae-presidents-delhi-hotel-stopped-by-security-when-4378953%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Saudi%20Arabian%20national%20on%20Saturday%20entered%20the%20five-star%20hotel%20where%20UAE%20President%20Mohamed%20bin%20Zayed%20Al%20Nahyan%20was%20staying%20and%20was%20stopped%20by%20security%20personnel%20while%20trying%20to%20approach%20him%20in%20the%20hotel%20lobby.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsaudi-cop-reaches-uae-presidents-delhi-hotel-stopped-by-security-when-4378953%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsaudi-cop-reaches-uae-presidents-delhi-hotel-stopped-by-security-when-4378953%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsaudi-cop-reaches-uae-presidents-delhi-hotel-stopped-by-security-when-4378953%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20G20%20Has%20Summarily%20Failed%20to%20Address%20Agrarian%20Distress%20in%20its%20Member%20Countries%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F11125829%2FUntitled-design-1-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENew%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20hosting%20of%20the%20G20%20summit%20opened%20a%20window%20to%20observe%20India%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20goals.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20summit%20was%20broken%20by%20the%20absence%20of%20Chinese%20and%20Russian%20presidents%20Vladimir%20Putin%20and%20Xi%20Jinping%2C%20but%20it%20did%20host%20world%20leaders%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fus-president-biden-says-he-raised-importance-of-human-rights-and-free-press-with-pm-modi%5C%22%3Eincluding%20the%20US%20president%20Joe%20Biden%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20all%20practical%20purposes%2C%20it%20is%20a%20known%20fact%20that%20the%20G20%20is%20the%20G7%20hiding%20in%20G20%E2%80%99s%20clothing%20and%20also%20pushing%20what%20is%20largely%20regarded%20as%20an%20American-Quad%20playbook.%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20various%20remarks%20to%20the%20US%20media%20before%20arriving%20in%20India%20had%20overtly%20expressed%20his%20desire%20to%20put%20%E2%80%9CAmerica%20first%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20G20.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20a%20successful%20BRICS%20conference%20in%20South%20Africa%2C%20complete%20with%20the%20addition%20of%20new%20members%2C%20US%20foreign%20policy%20had%20been%20keen%20to%20exert%20Quad%20influence%20on%20the%20G20%20too.%20Although%20the%20Russian%20and%20Chinese%20sides%20have%20come%20away%20with%20a%20significant%20victory%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fg20-modi-new-delhi-declaration-consensus%5C%22%3Ewith%20how%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20was%20handled%20in%20the%20New%20Delhi%20Declaration%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20agriculture%20diplomacy%20in%20the%20run%20up%20to%20the%20G20%20shows%20that%20it%20has%20always%20been%20angling%20at%20honouring%20the%20G7%E2%80%99s%20motto.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBacking%20up%20to%20June%2C%20when%20G20%E2%80%99s%20agricultural%20ministers%20met%20in%20Hyderabad%2C%20it%20became%20clear%20that%20we%20had%20a%20major%20diplomatic%20and%20imminent%20global%20food%20crisis.%20This%20is%20because%20no%20global%20food%20system%20can%20reasonably%20function%20in%20current%20times%20without%20Russian%20wheat%20and%20fertilisers.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Russia%2C%20on%20September%209%20rejected%20the%20United%20Nation%E2%80%99s%20timely%20offer%20to%20restart%20the%20%E2%80%98Black%20Sea%20Grain%20Deal%E2%80%99%20until%20the%20West%20and%20Ukraine%20de-escalate%20and%20meet%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20demands.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20even%20before%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20plane%20took%20off%2C%20India%20withdrew%20major%20custom%20duties%20on%20agricultural%20products%20of%20US%20origin%20like%20frozen%20turkey%2C%20frozen%20duck%2C%20blueberries%20and%20cranberries%20(of%20the%20fresh%2C%20frozen%2C%20dried%20and%20processed%20varieties)%20among%20other%20things.%20This%20is%20the%20second%20round%20of%20custom%20duty%20reductions%20in%20the%20past%20three%20months.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20could%20very%20well%20be%20that%20the%20move%20was%20crafted%20to%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20Joe%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20gains%20as%2C%20often%2C%20Indian%20consumers%20have%20to%20carry%20the%20burden%20of%20US-India%20friendships.%20US%20presidents%20have%2C%20over%20the%20years%2C%20pressured%20India%20to%20open%20up%20its%20agro-trade%20protections.%20It%20is%20in%20their%20interest%20to%20get%20Indians%20to%20buy%20US-origin%20farm%20goods%20%E2%80%93%20along%20with%20the%20other%20staple%2C%20arms.%20Thus%2C%20agriculturally%20speaking%2C%20India%20did%20give%20the%20US%20president%20a%20red%20carpet%20welcome.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20June%2C%20India%20had%20reduced%20custom%20duties%20on%20US%20agri-commodities%20including%20chickpeas%2C%20lentils%2C%20almonds%2C%20walnuts%20and%20apples.%20This%20allowed%20for%20imports%20to%20flood%20Indian%20markets.%20It%20was%20not%20by%20accident%20that%20the%20June%20G20%20agriculture%20ministers%E2%80%99%20meeting%20was%20held%20within%20days%20of%20this%20announcement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGetting%20back%20to%20G20%20New%20Delhi%2C%20another%20important%20agrarian%20buzz%20was%20the%20launch%20of%20the%20Global%20Biofuel%20Alliance.%20This%20clearly%20seems%20to%20also%20have%20been%20a%20move%20to%20please%20the%20US.%20India%20currently%20battles%20deep%20malnutrition%2C%20hyper%20food%20inflation%20and%20bad%20harvests%2C%20yet%20the%20message%20we%20are%20sending%20to%20the%20world%20and%20its%20own%20farmers%20is%20%E2%80%93%20we%20want%20to%20convert%20arable%20land%20for%20ethanol%20production%20and%20not%20food.%20The%20US%20has%20major%20interest%20in%20biofuel%20and%20the%20boost%20of%20a%20robust%20biofuel%20industry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20we%20simply%20examine%20the%20power%20dynamic%20within%20the%20alliance%2C%20it%20is%20evident%20that%20the%20US%20and%20US-based%20biofuel%20industry%20gets%20the%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share%20in%20policy%20decisions%20and%20is%20almost%20setting%20the%20agenda.%20Brazil%20is%20also%20rallying%20to%20the%20US%20because%20it%20is%20a%20major%20producer%20of%20bio-fuel.%20All%20the%20while%2C%20Indian%20policy%20makers%20are%20aptly%20parroting%20US%20policies.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbesindia.com%2Famp%2Farticle%2Flifes%2Fwhy-biofuels-might-not-be-so-green-after-all%2F86377%2F1%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etechnology%20is%20neither%20green%2C%20nor%20more%20beneficial%20for%20the%20Indian%20setting%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Plus%20exporting%20or%20importing%20biofuels%20is%20not%20a%20wise%20step%20for%20our%20economy%20or%20farmers.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fmodi-agriculture-wto-msp-policies-niti-aayog%5C%22%3EIs%20Indian%20Agriculture%20Following%20Two%20Policies%20%E2%80%93%20One%20at%20WTO%20and%20Another%20at%20Home%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20action%20since%20meeting%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20next%20important%20deadlock%20on%20agriculture%20is%20the%20follow%20up%20on%20the%20G20%20agriculture%20ministers%E2%80%99%20meeting.%20The%20outcome%20document%20read%20well%20and%20promoted%20%E2%80%9Cprinciples%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20practical%20solutions%20to%20address%20growing%20food%20security%20and%20agrarian%20issues%20seemed%20not%20to%20be%20in%20focus.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20personally%20said%20at%20the%20G20%20agriculture%20ministers%E2%80%99%20meeting%20that%20%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20G20%20priorities%20in%20agriculture%20focus%20on%20healing%20our%20%E2%80%98One%20Earth%E2%80%99%2C%20creating%20harmony%20within%20our%20%E2%80%98One%20Family%E2%80%99%20and%20giving%20hope%20for%20a%20bright%20%E2%80%98One%20Future%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20also%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CTraditional%20practices%20from%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20world%20may%20inspire%20us%20to%20develop%20alternatives%20for%20regenerative%20agriculture%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20even%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CFarmers%20all%20over%20India%20are%20taking%20up%20natural%20farming%20now.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%2C%20no%20steps%20were%20taken%20to%20formalise%20a%20global%20regenerative%20agriculture%20alliance%20in%20the%20final%20New%20Delhi%20Declaration.%20The%20document%20instead%20says%20that%20member%20countries%2C%20%E2%80%9CRecognize%20the%20importance%20of%20sustainable%20biofuels%20in%20our%20zero%20and%20low-emission%20development%20strategies%2C%20and%20note%20the%20setting%20up%20of%20a%20Global%20Biofuels%20Alliance.%E2%80%9D%20Notably%2C%20%E2%80%98agriculture%E2%80%99%20is%20only%20mentioned%20a%20grand%20total%20of%20six%20times%20in%20the%20document%20%E2%80%93%20three%20of%20which%20are%20direct%20mentions%20of%20the%20earlier%20agriculture%20ministers%E2%80%99%20and%20scientists%E2%80%99%20meetings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20clear%20to%20me%20that%20Modi%20wanted%20to%20promote%20industrial%20agriculture%20through%20the%20biofuel%20industry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFarmers%20should%20also%20be%20watchful%20as%20the%20outcome%20document%20put%20India%20on%20the%20path%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdigitalisation%20of%20agriculture%E2%80%9D%20which%20could%20not%20be%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20millions%20of%20farmers%20in%20the%20G20%20nations%20who%20don%E2%80%99t%20even%20own%20a%20smartphone.%20Plus%20they%20offer%20up%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20highest%20number%20of%20farmers%20for%20big%20tech%20grabs.%20This%20policy%20seems%20like%20an%20imposition%2C%20as%20no%20farmers%20were%20involved%20in%20this%20decision.%20If%20not%20for%20a%20forced%20demonetisation%2C%20Indian%20farmers%20would%20not%20have%20accepted%20the%20digital%20payments%20at%20all.%20Digitalisation%20in%20developing%20G20%20countries%20will%20have%20huge%20social%20and%20economic%20costs%20as%20education%20and%20digital%20literacy%20is%20already%20low%20and%20oftentimes%20underprivileged%20groups%20get%20left%20out%20from%20digitalisation%20drives.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERecently%2C%20it%20was%20reported%20that%20the%20leaders%20in%20New%20Delhi%20G20%20were%20talking%20of%20global%20food%20security%20threatened%20by%20growing%20poverty%2C%20climate%20change%2C%20pandemics%20and%20conflicts%2C%20but%20so%20far%20no%20decision%20on%20the%20action%20plan%20has%20come.%20Russian%20food%20and%20agri%20supplies%20may%20ameliorate%20the%20problem%2C%20but%20it%20seems%20they%20were%20blocked%20again.%20G20%20could%20have%20provided%20an%20important%20platform%20for%20food%20aid%20reducing%20world%20hunger%20not%20only%20in%20spirit%20but%20through%20a%20more%20concrete%20step.%20Apart%20from%20Russian%20wheat%2C%20Indian%20farmers%20could%20have%20played%20a%20big%20role%20in%20providing%20for%20nutrition%20needs%20of%20other%20developing%20G20%20nations.%20Other%20countries%20like%20Canada%2C%20Brazil%2C%20and%20perhaps%20Argentina%20could%20have%20pitched%20in%20and%20created%20a%20global%20food%20bank%20or%20reserve%20to%20help%20store%20grain%2C%20stabilise%20prices%20and%20supply%20a%20member%20nation%20when%20in%20need.%20But%20a%20consensus%20was%20not%20reached.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20rumour%20is%20if%20US%20wheat%20production%20increases%2C%20the%20necessity%20of%20Russian%20wheat%20will%20diminish.%20And%20Biden%20could%20offer%20the%20farmers%20a%20huge%20grain%20deal%20to%20keep%20them%20happy.%20So%20another%20geo-political%20battle%20is%20on%20between%20the%20grain%20giants%20over%20filling%20the%20wheat%20vacuum%20in%20the%20international%20markets.%20And%20over%20whether%20India%20could%20receive%20US%20wheat%20instead%20of%20Russian%20wheat%20consignments%2C%20when%20needed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20sum%20it%20up%2C%20the%20G20%20is%20a%20blessing%20for%20US%20agro-traders%2C%20big%20agricultural%20corporations%20and%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20electorate%20base%3B%20what%20it%20does%20for%20curtailing%20global%20hunger%20or%20Indian%20farmers%20is%20hard%20to%20say.%20Without%20a%20global%20consensus%20on%20food%20security%20and%20agrarian%20climate%20distress%2C%20hunger%20around%20the%20world%20will%20only%20grow.%20Once%20developing%20nations%20face%20the%20brunt%20of%20more%20hunger%2C%20diplomatic%20integrity%20and%20G20%20goals%20will%20be%20abandoned%20for%20bilateral%20agreements.%20Promises%20made%20in%20the%20calm%20will%20be%20forgotten%20at%20stormy%20times.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIndra%20Shekhar%20Singh%20is%20an%20independent%20agri-policy%20analyst%20and%20writer.%20He%20was%20the%20former%20director%20of%20policy%20and%20outreach%2C%20NSAI.%20He%20also%20hosts%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Wire%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eagriculture%20talk%20show%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EKrishi%20ki%20baat%2FFarm%20Talks%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20He%20tweets%20%40indrassingh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694417670000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fg20-farmers-agriculture-bio-fuel-india-us%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%E2%80%99s%20personal%20goals%2C%20especially%2C%20seem%20to%20have%20been%20steamrolled%20in%20favour%20of%20US%20policy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22