nt-after-g20-finance-ministers-meeting-due-to-ukraine-war%5C%22%3EG20%20ministerial%20meetings%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20Indian%20presidency%20%E2%80%93%20was%20languaged%20over%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20was%20acceptable%20to%20Russia%20and%20China.%20Unlike%20in%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20Bali%20Declaration%20in%20which%20Russia%20was%20described%20as%20the%20aggressor%20and%20asked%20to%20withdraw%20its%20troops%20from%20Ukraine%20fully%20and%20unconditionally%2C%20the%20New%20Delhi%20Declaration%20called%20it%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20war%20in%20Ukraine%E2%80%9D.%20There%20was%20no%20condemnation%20of%20Russia%20either%2C%20unlike%20in%20Bali.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20consensus%20reflected%20an%20eagerness%20in%20the%20Western%20bloc%20to%20prevent%20the%20impression%20of%20a%20breakdown%20of%20the%20G20%20in%20India%2C%20a%20country%20that%20the%20US%20is%20wooing%20assiduously%20for%20its%20geopolitical%20goal%20of%20containing%20China.%20The%20US%20and%20other%20Western%20members%20of%20the%20G20%20agreed%20to%20the%20watering%20down%20of%20the%20language%20on%20the%20war%20to%20help%20India%20score%20a%20diplomatic%20victory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20EU%20diplomat%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20helped%20too%20to%20avoid%20unfavourable%20comparisons%20with%20the%20China-dominated%20BRICS%20%E2%80%93%20despite%20being%20projected%20as%20%E2%80%9Cfractious%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20grouping%20managed%20a%20joint%20declaration%20at%20its%20summit%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20return%20gift%20to%20the%20West%20was%20the%20announcement%20during%20one%20of%20the%20G20%20summit%20sessions%20of%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-us-economic-corridor-west-asia-europe%5C%22%3Eambitious%20economic%20corridor%3C%2Fa%3E%20linking%20the%20EU%2C%20Middle%20East%20and%20India%20physically%20by%20rail%20and%20waterways%2C%20and%20to%20economically%20through%20trade%20and%20digital%20infrastructure%20and%20politically%20bring%20the%20three%20together%2C%20a%20geopolitical%20rival%20to%20the%20Chinese%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiative.%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20called%20it%20%E2%80%9Ca%20really%20big%20deal%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20there%20is%20no%20timeline%20to%20its%20completion%20and%20no%20details%20are%20available%20yet%20about%20the%20funding.%20It%20is%20to%20include%20India%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%20(with%20whom%20the%20US%20is%20trying%20to%20repair%20its%20relations)%2C%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20Jordan%2C%20Israel%20and%20the%20European%20Union.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20presidency%20is%20now%20seen%20as%20the%20point%20at%20which%20the%20G20%E2%80%99s%20agenda%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Fsep%2F10%2Fwatered-down-g20-statement-on-ukraine-is-sign-of-indias-growing-influence%5C%22%3Ebegan%20to%20transition%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20being%20set%20and%20directed%20by%20the%20wealthy%20G7%20nations%20that%20have%20dominated%20it%20from%20inception%20to%20become%20more%20representative%20of%20the%20developing%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EForeign%20minister%20Sergei%20Lavrov%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20Russian%20delegation%2C%20said%20the%20summit%20was%20a%20success%20for%20India%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20developing%20countries.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Global%20South%E2%80%99s%20position%20in%20the%20talks%20helped%20prevent%20the%20G20%20agenda%20from%20being%20overshadowed%20by%20Ukraine%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Frussia-says-g20-declaration-balanced-summit-moves-final-day-2023-09-10%2F%5C%22%3Ehe%20told%20a%20press%20conference%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20has%20truly%20consolidated%20G20%20members%20from%20the%20Global%20South.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Weakening%20on%20Russia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20summit%20declaration%20not%20only%20reflected%20the%20developing%20world%E2%80%99s%20position%20on%20the%20war%2C%20it%20may%20also%20be%20an%20early%20signal%20on%20a%20shift%20in%20the%20US%20and%20the%20West.%20Western%20media%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F08%2F04%2Fukraine-war-us-spending%2F%5C%22%3Enoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20softening%20of%20language%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20further%20signal%20that%20as%20Joe%20Biden%20faces%20an%20election%20year%2C%20Ukraine%20is%20perceptibly%20slipping%20down%20his%20list%20of%20foreign%20policy%20priorities%20as%20the%20need%20grows%20to%20nurture%20alliances%20to%20contain%20China%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20poured%20billions%20of%20dollars%20into%20the%20Ukrainian%20war%20effort.%20But%20with%20Russia%20proving%20it%20cannot%20be%20defeated%20in%20the%20battlefield%20and%20the%20Ukrainians%20unable%20to%20demonstrate%20a%20win%20in%20the%20last%20nine%20months%2C%20public%20fatigue%20is%20beginning%20to%20show%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20and%20European%20officials%20publicly%20defended%20the%20language%20on%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20and%20were%20emphatic%20that%20it%20was%20not%20a%20victory%20for%20Russia.%20White%20House%20national%20security%20adviser%20Jake%20Sullivan%20told%20reporters%20the%20summit%20declaration%20%E2%80%9Cdoes%20a%20very%20good%20job%20of%20standing%20up%20for%20the%20principle%20that%20states%20cannot%20use%20force%20to%20seek%20territorial%20acquisition%20or%20to%20violate%20the%20territorial%20integrity%20and%20sovereignty%20or%20political%20independence%20of%20other%20states%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrench%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20said%20the%20G20%20declaration%20had%20isolated%20Russia.%20He%20said%20the%20G20%20is%20not%20necessarily%20a%20forum%20for%20political%20discussions%20where%20diplomatic%20progress%20can%20be%20expected%20on%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20here%20to%20talk%20about%20economic%20topics%20and%20the%20climate%20(crisis).%20G20%20should%20not%20get%20stuck%20on%20these%20issues%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20sense%20that%20western%20pressure%20on%20Russia%20had%20eased%20was%20evident%20in%20the%20Russian%20foreign%20minister%E2%80%99s%20triumphant%20tone.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20able%20to%20prevent%20the%20west%E2%80%99s%20attempts%20to%20%E2%80%98Ukrainise%E2%80%99%20the%20summit%20agenda%2C%E2%80%9D%20Lavrov%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUkraine%2C%20insecure%20about%20being%20possibly%20abandoned%2C%20senses%20the%20downgrading%20better%20than%20anyone%20else%2C%20which%20is%20why%20it%20was%20quick%20to%20denounce%20the%20Declaration%20as%20%E2%80%9Cnothing%20to%20be%20proud%20of%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Other%20contenders%20to%20%E2%80%9Cvoice%20of%20the%20Global%20South%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20the%20myriad%20reasons%20for%20the%20Delhi%20summit%E2%80%99s%20success%2C%20the%20excessive%20projection%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20billboards%20across%20the%20capital%20and%20in%20every%20state%20where%20the%20G20%20officials%20held%20meetings%20ahead%20of%20the%20summit%20were%20any%20indication%2C%20the%20achievement%20of%20papering%20over%20the%20geopolitical%20divide%20is%20certain%20to%20be%20projected%20by%20the%20Modi%20government%20and%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20upcoming%20election%20season%20as%20a%20victory%20for%20Modi%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20acceptance%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cvishwaguru%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20world%20and%20leader%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cglobal%20south%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20Modi-led%20India%20is%20not%20alone%20in%20claiming%20to%20be%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20developing%20world.%20This%20space%20is%20crowded.%20The%20New%20Delhi%20Declaration%20would%20not%20have%20been%20possible%20had%20it%20not%20been%20for%20the%20support%20India%20received%20from%20Brazil%2C%20Indonesia%20and%20South%20Africa.%20In%20his%20press%20conference%20on%20Saturday%2C%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20named%20these%20countries%20with%20which%20India%20had%20a%20%E2%80%9Cstrong%20history%20of%20working%20together%E2%80%9D%20as%20he%20thanked%20all%20members%20for%20their%20efforts%20to%20bring%20a%20consensus.%20These%20countries%20also%20represent%20the%20reality%20that%20the%20global%20South%20is%20not%20a%20monolith%20and%20each%20has%20its%20own%20ambitions%20on%20the%20global%20stage.%20Indonesia%20held%20the%202022%20G20%20presidency%2C%20and%20using%20its%20ASEAN%20presidency%2C%20has%20taken%20the%20lead%20to%20resolve%20the%20failure%20in%20Myanmar.%20With%20a%20population%20of%20280%20million%2C%20it%20is%20the%20largest%20Muslim%20country%2C%20and%20the%20fourth%20most%20populous%20country%20in%20the%20world.%20It%20takes%20pride%20in%20having%20overthrown%20a%20US-backed%20corrupt%20military%20ruler%20and%20established%20itself%20as%20a%20democracy%20%E2%80%94%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20third%20largest%20%E2%80%94%20that%20takes%20pride%20in%20its%20ethnic%20and%20religious%20diversity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndonesia%E2%80%99s%20economy%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Fleaders%2F2022%2F11%2F17%2Fwhy-indonesia-matters%5C%22%3Egrowing%20at%20a%20steady%20clip%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Unlike%20India%2C%20it%20continues%20to%20take%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Feconomy%2F2023%2F8%2F28%2Findonesias-absence-from-bigger-brics-echoesdecadesof-non-alignedpolicy%5C%22%3Einspiration%20from%20its%20non-aligned%20past%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20well%20as%20from%20its%20independence%20leader%20first%20President%20Sukarno%2C%20and%20uses%20its%20strategic%20location%20in%20the%20Malacca%20straits%20to%20do%20business%20with%20both%20China%20and%20the%20US%2C%20declining%20to%20be%20part%20of%20any%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBrazil%2C%20which%20takes%20over%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20G20%20from%20India%20later%20this%20year%2C%20is%20the%20sixth%20most%20populous%20country%20in%20the%20world%20with%20(population%20217%20million)%2C%20and%20is%20the%20most%20influential%20country%20in%20Latin%20America.%20Its%20leftist%20president%20Luiz%20In%C3%A1cio%20Lula%20da%20Silva%2C%20known%20as%20Lula%2C%20is%20a%20big%20hitter%20in%20the%20global%20arena.%20A%20firm%20multilateralist%20who%20believes%20in%20%3Cem%3Ediplomacia%20activa%20e%20altiva%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20foreign%20policy%20that%20is%20active%20and%20prominent)%2C%20he%20has%20begun%20undoing%20his%20predecessor%20Jair%20Bolsanaoro%E2%80%99s%20insular%20foreign%20policy%20and%20restoring%20Brazil%E2%80%99s%20place%20in%20the%20world%2C%20as%20an%20influential%20voice%20of%20the%20developing%20world.%20%E2%80%98Brazil%20is%20Back%E2%80%99%20is%20his%20foreign%20policy%20slogan.%20Indeed%2C%20he%20was%20an%20early%20claimant%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cvoice%20of%20the%20Global%20South%E2%80%9D%20in%20his%20previous%20terms%20from%202003-2010%2C%20when%20he%20spearheaded%20efforts%20to%20strengthen%20BRICS%20and%20Brazil%E2%80%99s%20place%20in%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20aspirant%20for%20a%20permanent%20seat%20in%20the%20United%20Nations%20like%20India%2C%20Brazil%20has%20taken%20a%20neutral%20stance%20over%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20It%20supported%20a%20US-sponsored%20UN%20resolution%20in%20February%202022%20demanding%20that%20Russia%20withdraw%20its%20troops%20from%20Ukraine%2C%20but%20Lula%20has%20also%20criticised%20the%20US%20%E2%80%93%20during%20a%20visit%20to%20China%20%E2%80%93%20for%20%E2%80%9Cencouraging%E2%80%9D%20Ukraine.%20Like%20Modi%2C%20Lula%20wants%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20making%20efforts%20to%20end%20the%20war.%20He%20has%20called%20for%20diplomatic%20efforts%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpeace%20club%E2%80%9D%20of%20neutral%20nations%20to%20broker%20an%20end%20to%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELula%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Faug%2F08%2Fbrazilian-president-lula-pledges-new-amazon-dream-at-rainforest-summits%5C%22%3Ereverse%20the%20plunder%20of%20the%20Amazon%20rainforest%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2060%25%20of%20which%20falls%20in%20Brazil%2C%20makes%20him%20a%20valuable%20partner%20of%20the%20West%20on%20climate%20change%20mitigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20world%20will%20be%20watching%20to%20see%20how%20Brazil%E2%80%99s%20presidency%20unfolds.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FANI%2Fstatus%2F1700776510591004822%5C%22%3Ehis%20speech%20at%20the%20summit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Lula%20identified%20%E2%80%9Cinequality%E2%80%9D%20as%20the%20root%20cause%20of%20all%20the%20problems%20facing%20the%20world%2C%20and%20has%20already%20outlined%20the%20priorities%20for%20the%20Rio%20summit%3A%20social%20inclusion%20and%20fight%20against%20hunger%3B%20energy%20transition%20and%20sustainable%20development%3B%20the%20reform%20of%20global%20governance%20institutions.%20Two%20task%20forces%20will%20be%20created%20%E2%80%93%20Global%20Alliance%20against%20Hunger%20and%20Poverty%20and%20the%20Global%20Mobilisation%20against%20Climate%20Change.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20AU%20membership%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20entry%20of%20the%20African%20Union%20is%20seen%20as%20one%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20outcomes%20of%20the%20Delhi%20summit.%20India%20takes%20credit%20for%20backing%20the%20membership%20of%20the%20Union%20which%20is%20a%20grouping%20of%20all%2055%20African%20countries%2C%20which%20have%20a%20c%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fg20-membership-africa-economy-india-ae58459261bc2722b54da422debc5b83%5C%22%3Eombined%20GDP%20of%20%242.99%20trillion%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20membership%2C%20sought%20by%20the%20AU%20for%20seven%20years%2C%20was%20welcomed%20by%20Senegal%20President%20Macky%20Sall%2C%20the%20previous%20AU%20chair%20who%20helped%20to%20push%20for%20membership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20the%20AU%20can%20do%20for%20the%20continent%20as%20a%20G20%20member%20will%20depend%20on%20what%20extent%20it%20can%20forge%20common%20positions%20between%20its%20members.%20There%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fis-the-african-union-at-risk-of-failing-in-its-role-as-a-mediator%2Fa-65730521%5C%22%3Equestions%20about%20AU%E2%80%99s%20leadership%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20on%20questions%20of%20peace%20and%20security%20in%20the%20continent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20will%20also%20depend%20on%20how%20South%20Africa%2C%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20economies%20in%20the%20continent%20which%20also%20aspires%20to%20a%20permanent%20UNSC%20membership%2C%20perceives%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20new%20entrant%20on%20its%20standing%20in%20the%20grouping.%20A%20commentator%20on%20South%20Africa%20Broadcasting%20Corporation%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DAnTSQY6bsAE%5C%22%3Esuggested%20the%20G20%20had%20%E2%80%9Csent%20a%20message%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20President%20Cyril%20Ramaphosa%20by%20making%20the%20AU%20a%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20China%E2%80%99s%20silent%20presence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20stay%20away%20from%20the%20summit%2C%20and%20downgrade%20China%E2%80%99s%20participation%20to%20the%20level%20of%20Premier%20Li%20Qiang%2C%20was%20a%20sign%20that%20despite%20the%20bonhomie%20of%20the%20consensus%20at%20the%20Delhi%20Declaration%2C%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20geopolitical%20divide%20remains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20with%20its%20close%20embrace%20of%20the%20US%20despite%20a%20careful%20balancing%20act%2C%20is%20right%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20it.%20Ahead%20of%20the%20summit%2C%20a%20Chinese%20think%20tank%20affiliated%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20State%20Security%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Fchina-think-tank-says-india-is-sabotaging-g20-its-own-agenda-2023-09-09%2F%5C%22%3Eaccused%20Delhi%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20using%20its%20G20%20presidency%20to%20to%20bring%20geopolitical%20%E2%80%9Cprivate%20goods%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20global%20agenda%2C%20an%20apparent%20reference%20to%20the%20holding%20of%20summit%20meetings%20in%20Arunachal%20and%20J%26amp%3BK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20China%20also%20signed%20off%20on%20the%20consensus%20document%2C%20messaging%20it%20was%20not%20making%20itself%20available%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cspoiler%E2%80%9D%20tag.%20Premier%20Li%20did%20not%20offer%20any%20comments%20on%20the%20Declaration.%20And%20against%20its%20reported%20earlier%20objections%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20use%20of%20the%20Sanskrit%20phrase%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EVasudaiva%20Kutumbakam%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98%2C%20Beijing%20seems%20to%20have%20decided%20to%20deploy%20the%20phrase%20for%20its%20own%20purposes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CVasudhaiva%20Kutumbakam%2C%20a%20Sanskrit%20phrase%20from%20ancient%20Indian%20scriptures%2C%20means%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20world%20is%20one%20family%E2%80%9D.%20The%20theme%20of%20the%20Indian%20G20%20Summit%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9COne%20Earth%2C%20One%20Family%2C%20One%20Future%E2%80%9D%20in%20English%20%E2%80%93%20underscores%20the%20expectation%20that%20countries%20will%20support%20each%20other%20in%20pursuing%20growth.%20Mutual%20assistance%20in%20pursuing%20growth%20as%20%E2%80%9COne%20Family%E2%80%9D%20is%20more%20imperative%20nowadays%2C%E2%80%9D%20Xinhua%2C%20the%20Chinese%20state%20news%20agency%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenglish.news.cn%2F20230909%2F1b6850c197544f6087a68743178cd0d2%2Fc.html%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20a%20commentary%20on%20the%20summit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20arguing%20that%20it%20was%20the%20US%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Chigh%20fence%2C%20small%20yard%E2%80%9D%20protectionist%20policies%20that%20were%20causing%20the%20global%20instability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENirupama%20Subramanian%20is%20an%20independent%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694413195000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F