0the%20internal%20palladium.%20The%20MRI%20scan%20does%20not%20belong%20to%20Johnson.%3Cp%3EBSIP%2FUIG%20Via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20development%20in%20neurotechnology%20has%20given%20a%20stroke%20survivor%20her%20voice%20back%20after%20nearly%2020%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20woman%20had%20a%20brain%20stem%20stroke%20that%20left%20her%20paralyzed%20and%20unable%20to%20speak%20at%20age%2030.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHer%20new%20implant%20uses%20AI%20to%20decode%20brain%20signals%20and%20convert%20them%20to%20computerized%20speech.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20two%20decades%20ago%2C%20then-30-year-old%20Ann%20Johnson%20had%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2F20-year-old-stroke-symptoms-dismissed-as-migraine-coma-2022-4%5C%22%3Ebrain%20stem%20stroke%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20though%20she%20survived%2C%20she%20was%20left%20paralyzed%20and%20unable%20to%20speak%20with%20a%20condition%20known%20as%20locked-in%20syndrome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohnson%20slowly%20regained%20the%20ability%20to%20breathe%20independently%2C%20move%20her%20neck%2C%20and%20wink%2C%20but%20after%2018%20years%2C%20her%20brain%20hasn't%20recovered%20its%20ability%20to%20move%20the%20muscles%20required%20for%20her%20to%20speak%20more%20than%20a%20few%20words.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20help%20of%20a%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneuralink-elon-musk-microchips-brains-ai-2021-2%5C%22%3EAI-driven%20brain%20implant%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20has%20become%20the%20first%20patient%20to%20successfully%20use%20a%20groundbreaking%20neurotechnology%20that%20synthesizes%20speech%20and%20facial%20expressions%20from%20brain%20signals%2C%20the%20researchers%20behind%20the%20project%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20study%20published%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3De0d9c491881fa19aa753e5562ed3f91cc50675ab086fa7c14b0e63a7139d6dea%26postID%3D64fe3dae261711ba2f64679b%26postSlug%3Dai-neurotech-allows-stroke-survivor-speak-brainwaves-thinking-paralyzed-2023-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41586-023-06443-4%5C%22%3ENature%3C%2Fa%3E%20late%20last%20month%2C%20researchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%20San%20Francisco%20and%20the%20University%20of%20California%20Berkeley%20detailed%20their%20findings%20after%20implanting%20a%20thin%20layer%20of%20253%20electrodes%20on%20Johnson's%20brain%20and%20customizing%20the%20technology%20to%20read%20her%20brain%20signals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fbrain-computer-interface-what-is-it-how-does-it-work-2022-9%5C%22%3Eneurotechnology%20uses%20artificial%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20decode%20the%20woman's%20brain%20signals%20while%20she%20tries%20to%20speak.%20Though%20her%20muscles%20don't%20move%2C%20her%20brain%20sends%20a%20signal%20perceptible%20to%20the%20electrodes%2C%20which%20decode%20what%20she%20is%20trying%20to%20say%2C%20and%20then%20synthesizes%20speech%20and%20facial%20expressions%20using%20a%20computer-generated%20avatar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohnson%2C%20who%20doesn't%20have%20cognitive%20or%20sensory%20impairment%20after%20the%20stroke%2C%20could%20previously%20communicate%20at%20roughly%2014%20words%20per%20minute%20using%20her%20old%20typing%20method%20involving%20a%20device%20that%20responds%20to%20small%20head%20movements%2C%20per%20a%20University%20of%20California%20San%20Francisco%20news%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ucsf.edu%2Fnews%2F2023%2F08%2F425986%2Fhow-artificial-intelligence-gave-paralyzed-woman-her-voice-back%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20breakthrough.%20With%20her%20new%20implant%2C%20her%20digital%20avatar%20speaks%20almost%2080.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20goal%20is%20to%20restore%20a%20full%2C%20embodied%20way%20of%20communicating%2C%20which%20is%20the%20most%20natural%20way%20for%20us%20to%20talk%20with%20others%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Edward%20Chang%2C%20chair%20of%20neurological%20surgery%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%20San%20Francisco%2C%20said%20in%20the%20UCSF%20publication%20about%20the%20research.%20%26quot%3BThese%20advancements%20bring%20us%20much%20closer%20to%20making%20this%20a%20real%20solution%20for%20patients.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChang%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20UCSF%20and%20UCB%20researchers%20claim%20Johnson's%20case%20is%20a%20scientific%20first%20for%20allowing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flocked-in-brain-implant-talk-study-controversial-lou-gehrigs-als-2022-3%5C%22%3Epeople%20with%20locked-in%20syndrome%20to%20communicate%20using%20neurotechnology%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20two%20researchers%20from%20Austria's%20Wyss%20Center%20for%20Bio%20and%20Neuroengineering%20claimed%20last%20year%20they%20had%20achieved%20a%20similar%20feat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20their%20results%20working%20with%20a%2034-year-old%20man%20to%20regain%20his%20ability%20to%20speak%20after%20being%20paralyzed%20were%20promising%2C%20the%20Austrian%20researchers%20previously%20had%20a%20paper%20on%20the%20subject%20retracted%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bseveral%20cases%20of%20scientific%20misconduct%26quot%3B%20were%20identified%20in%20a%202019%20investigation%20conducted%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dfg.de%2Fservice%2Fpresse%2Fpressemitteilungen%2F2019%2Fpressemitteilung_nr_46%2Findex.html%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22130733c0b6cc2e1330d7fbfbb7aae431%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2280%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dfg.de%2Fservice%2Fpresse%2Fpressemitteilungen%2F2019%2Fpressemitteilung_nr_46%2Findex.html%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGerman%20Research%20Foundation%20(DFG)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20funded%20some%20of%20the%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrain-chips-elon-musk-neuralink-change-personality-behavior-computer-tech-2023-2%5C%22%3Eneurotechnology%20facing%20controversy%20and%20ethics%20concerns%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20developments%20in%20the%20public%20and%20private%20sectors%20have%20been%20identified%20by%20groups%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unesco.org%2Fen%2Fethics-neurotech%5C%22%3EUnited%20Nations%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20among%20the%20fastest-growing%20fields%20with%20the%20possibility%20to%20improve%20human%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20Johnson%2C%20the%20benefits%20of%20being%20involved%20in%20the%20UCSF%20project%20are%20far%20more%20expansive%20than%20just%20offering%20her%20the%20opportunity%20to%20speak%20again%20after%20all%20these%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20was%20at%20the%20rehab%20hospital%2C%20the%20speech%20therapist%20didn't%20know%20what%20to%20do%20with%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Johnson%20said%2C%20per%20the%20UCSF%20publication.%20%26quot%3BBeing%20a%20part%20of%20this%20study%20has%20given%20me%20a%20sense%20of%20purpose%2C%20I%20feel%20like%20I%20am%20contributing%20to%20society.%20It%20feels%20like%20I%20have%20a%20job%20again.%20It's%20amazing%20I%20have%20lived%20this%20long%3B%20this%20study%20has%20allowed%20me%20to%20really%20live%20while%20I'm%20still%20alive!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cfigure%20data-entity-type%3D%5C%22media%5C%22%20data-entity-uuid%3D%5C%222c277e1f-13f0-4fad-851b-b15e95d12b40%5C%22%20data-entity-embed-display-settings%3D%5C%22%7B%26quot%3Bimage_style%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3Bfull_bleed__image%26quot%3B%2C%26quot%3Bimage_link%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3B%26quot%3B%2C%26quot%3Bimage_loading%26quot%3B%3A%7B%26quot%3Battribute%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3Blazy%26quot%3B%7D%2C%26quot%3Blink_url%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3B%26quot%3B%7D%5C%22%20data-embed-button%3D%5C%22media_assets%5C%22%20data-entity-embed-display%3D%5C%22entity_reference%3Amedia_thumbnail%5C%22%20data-langcode%3D%